ce:section.ce:para:
We first studied the optimum detection conditions, such as pH and incubation time. The fluorescence intensities of sensing system without (F0) and with (F) the addition of alizarin red were recorded under different conditions. As suggested in Fig. S5, the F0-F reached the maximum value under the pH of 6 and incubation time of 30 s. So the above optimum detection conditions were applied for further experiments. As suggested in Fig. 3
                        A, the fluorescence emission spectra of measurement system with addition of different alizarin red concentrations were carried out. The fluorescence intensity appeared a weakening phenomenon with alizarin red concentrations increasing from 0 to 200 μM. In addition, we discussed the linear detection of alizarin red. The relationship between ln(F0/F) and alizarin red concentration was investigated. As we could see from Fig. 3B, a fascinating linear curve was developed between ln(F0/F) and alizarin red concentration in the range of 0.5–200 μM. The linear equation, fitting coefficient and LOD were ln(F0/F) = 0.0065[Q] + 0.047, 0.9955 and 0.064 μM, respectively. Compared with the published references, this fluorescence platform represented outstanding linear range and LOD (Table 1
                        ). The above results indicated that the FA@CuNCs could be applied as fluorescence platforms for the measurement of alizarin red in the actual environment.
